{"LERE":[{"def":"Learning; lesson; lore.","pos":""}],"LERNAEA":[{"def":"A Linnæan genus of parasitic Entomostraca, -- the same as the family Lernæidæ.","pos":""}],"LERNAEACEA":[{"def":"A suborder of copepod Crustacea, including a large number of remarkable forms, mostly parasitic on fishes.","pos":""}],"LERNEAN":[{"def":"One of a family (Lernæidæ) of parasitic Crustacea found attached to fishes and other marine animals.","pos":""}],"LEROT":[{"def":"A small European rodent (Eliomys nitela), allied to the dormouse.","pos":""}]}